ABAKALIKI – Ahead of Saturday’s presidential and National Assembly elections, the Ebonyi State chapter of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) has backed the decision of the National Executive Committee (NEC) of the party on the endorsement of President Muhammadu Buhari. DAILY INDEPENDENT reports that the NEC of the party recently dumped their presidential candidate and former Governor of Cross River State, Donald Duke, and declared support for President Buhari of the All Progressives Congress (APC). In a statement in Abakaliki on Tuesday, the chairman of the party in the state, Austin Ituma-Nweze, said Ebonyi chapter of SDP had also adopted President Buhari as its own presidential candidate and would mobilize for his victory in Saturday’s election.